1
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:04,333
[ground dragon
and rigers galloping]

2
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:10,166
- Just neow getting around
to joining us, Julius?

3
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:12,708
Thanks so much for gracing us
with your presence.

4
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:15,125
- Please. You're going
to ruin my reputation.

5
00:00:15,208 --> 00:00:17,708
Now listen.
You seem to be mistaken.

6
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:19,458
I am not the man called Julius.

7
00:00:19,541 --> 00:00:21,791
Let me see.

8
00:00:21,875 --> 00:00:24,541
Perhaps I'll go by something
like Jules instead.

9
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:27,208
Even if it is temporary,

10
00:00:27,291 --> 00:00:29,125
a man who has
the status of a knight

11
00:00:29,208 --> 00:00:33,416
must never lower himself to
the rank of a common mercenary.

12
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,416
The man you see
standing here before you

13
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,625
is not Julius Euclius,
the knight.

14
00:00:37,708 --> 00:00:39,625
I am but a simple wanderer
by the name of Jules.

15
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:41,875
- [groans]
- A proper household's

16
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,375
code of chivalry can be
a real pain sometimes, huh?

17
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,208
- What an utter load of crap.

18
00:00:46,291 --> 00:00:49,208
- It would seem you're doing
better than I expected.

19
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:50,791
Tell me, how are you feeling,
Subaru?

20
00:00:50,875 --> 00:00:52,666
- [gasps]

21
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,791
Well, it was
just some scratches.

22
00:00:54,875 --> 00:00:58,083
A little spit fixed
everything right up pretty much.

23
00:00:58,166 --> 00:00:59,583
And how have things
been with you

24
00:00:59,666 --> 00:01:01,083
since our
little disagreement, huh?

25
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:04,541
Busy apologizing for fighting
so seriously with an amateur?

26
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:07,375
- That's not
what I was asking about.

27
00:01:07,458 --> 00:01:08,500
I was referring to the damage
to your honor

28
00:01:08,583 --> 00:01:11,458
by the mabeast subjugation.

29
00:01:11,541 --> 00:01:13,333
[sighs]

30
00:01:13,416 --> 00:01:14,166
But I'm glad to hear your wounds

31
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:16,208
from our previous encounter
have healed.

32
00:01:18,708 --> 00:01:21,875
[both laugh]

33
00:01:21,958 --> 00:01:23,916
- [chanting]

34
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:32,541
- ♪ Now let me open the scar ♪

35
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:36,291
♪<i> Tokeatta</i> virus ♪

36
00:01:36,375 --> 00:01:38,125
[singing in Japanese]

37
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:22,583
♪ Now let me open the scar ♪

38
00:02:22,666 --> 00:02:25,583
♪<i> Tokeatta</i> virus ♪

39
00:02:25,666 --> 00:02:27,708
[singing in Japanese]

40
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:33,250
♪ Grew up in the loneliness ♪

41
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:35,250
[singing in Japanese]

42
00:02:53,583 --> 00:02:54,541
SUBARU: Thanks to all of you,

43
00:02:54,625 --> 00:02:55,750
we succeeded in taking out
the White Whale.

44
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:58,875
However, it's not over yet.

45
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:00,500
I have a score to settle

46
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:02,208
with those weirdoes
in the Witch's Cult

47
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:04,291
who decided
to pick a fight with me.

48
00:03:04,375 --> 00:03:05,375
Once that's done,

49
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:07,541
the White Whale subjugation
will be complete.

50
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:09,291
- The Witch's Cult is up next?!

51
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:10,166
- You think we can
trust the allegations

52
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:11,583
that the White Whale
and the Witch's Cult

53
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:13,791
are actually connected?

54
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:15,666
I mean, after all, we just
came here as reinforcements

55
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:17,750
- for the--
- Enough!

56
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:18,916
- Ow! What was that for?

57
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,416
- If you can't believe him,

58
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,916
ever after everything he did
to help stop the White Whale,

59
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,416
then you just need
to believe me.

60
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,250
- I'd prefer it
if you believed me

61
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,625
without you bashing
his head in, though.

62
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:29,333
[fists creak]

63
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:30,625
I don't like to recall it,

64
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:33,458
but I've run up against
the Witch's Cult once before.

65
00:03:33,541 --> 00:03:35,208
I found out then.

66
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:37,000
- Didn't you look into
that connection before,

67
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:38,708
Old Man Wil?

68
00:03:38,791 --> 00:03:41,541
- I wouldn't call my findings
definitive evidence,

69
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:43,458
but instances
of Whale appearances

70
00:03:43,541 --> 00:03:47,250
and cult activities seem
to coincide in many respects.

71
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:50,666
- I'd say that makes it
doubly credible.

72
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,958
And on that note,
we're going to make our way

73
00:03:53,041 --> 00:03:54,833
to the Mathers domain.

74
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:56,916
That cult is hiding
in the forest there.

75
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,833
The way to defeat them
is as simple as it gets.

76
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:02,750
We'll raid them before they
can read our movements

77
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:03,500
and crush them.

78
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:05,500
- I'm concerned.

79
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:06,666
Is there a way
to keep the villagers safe?

80
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:09,416
- Already taken care of.

81
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:10,291
I asked Miss Anastasia
and Russell

82
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,833
to talk to the merchants
along the highway.

83
00:04:13,708 --> 00:04:15,041
Under the condition
that Margrave Mathers

84
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:18,000
buys their cargo
at the asking price,

85
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:19,333
they'll ask the merchants

86
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:20,333
to evacuate
the villagers of Arlam

87
00:04:20,416 --> 00:04:22,750
as well as the residents
of Roswaal's mansion.

88
00:04:22,833 --> 00:04:25,416
For those in the mansion,

89
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,375
a messenger
from Miss Crusch's household

90
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:29,541
will deliver them
a handwritten letter.

91
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:31,833
Nobody there
knows about the alliance.

92
00:04:31,916 --> 00:04:33,458
If we don't notify them
about it,

93
00:04:33,541 --> 00:04:34,750
then there's bound to be chaos.

94
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:36,458
- Sounds like we can get
the ball rolling, then.

95
00:04:36,541 --> 00:04:38,458
BOTH: Yeah!

96
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:40,500
- We've quite
the upper hand here.

97
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:41,791
We've never had
such an advantage

98
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:43,333
battling the Witch's Cult.

99
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:46,041
- Yeah. And now with Julius
and his crew joining us,

100
00:04:46,125 --> 00:04:48,958
there's no way
we'll be outnumbered.

101
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:50,750
Hmm?

102
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,666
- I'd like to offer
one correction.

103
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:55,041
Remember my name is Jules.

104
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:57,875
Just be sure
to keep that in mind.

105
00:04:57,958 --> 00:04:59,875
- Back off with that!
It'll just be a hassle

106
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:01,541
in informal settings
like this one!

107
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:03,750
[sighs]

108
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:07,083
The battle with the White Whale
was a rough one.

109
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:07,708
I thought I was gonna die.

110
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:09,708
Unfortunately...

111
00:05:09,791 --> 00:05:12,375
some of us did.

112
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:14,750
Some others vanished,
never to return.

113
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:20,625
Let's take them down
without another death,

114
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:21,666
not one person.

115
00:05:22,166 --> 00:05:23,833
Let's win this thing

116
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:25,708
and all go back home alive!

117
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:28,541
[steeds galloping]

118
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:33,375
- I still can't believe

119
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,583
- that you actually defeated it.
- Huh?

120
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:36,375
- The subjugation
of the White Whale

121
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:38,625
has been a wish
the Imperial Knights

122
00:05:38,708 --> 00:05:39,916
have held for as long
as anyone can remember,

123
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,000
but were never able to fulfill.

124
00:05:42,083 --> 00:05:43,583
- [gasps]

125
00:05:43,666 --> 00:05:46,916
- It would seem
I owe you my thanks.

126
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,083
- Look, you don't
have to force it, okay?

127
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,708
- For putting an end
to what seemed

128
00:05:50,791 --> 00:05:51,875
like an unstoppable calamity

129
00:05:51,958 --> 00:05:54,083
that all nations ignored
for far too long,

130
00:05:54,166 --> 00:05:55,833
I sincerely thank you.

131
00:05:55,916 --> 00:05:57,125
- [gasps]

132
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:58,541
[grumbles]

133
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:04,083
I'm grateful to you,
too, I guess,

134
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:06,625
for coming to back us up,

135
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:09,125
even after what happened.

136
00:06:09,208 --> 00:06:10,875
About that, I was--

137
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:13,916
Aw, damn it all! Crap!

138
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,625
Listen, I know! I know, okay?!

139
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:18,791
I know it now, all right?!
[groans]

140
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:20,541
It was all my fault.

141
00:06:20,625 --> 00:06:22,625
Sorry. I--

142
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,958
I apologize.

143
00:06:25,916 --> 00:06:29,041
- As do I, genuinely.

144
00:06:29,125 --> 00:06:30,958
I can't take back
my words and actions.

145
00:06:31,041 --> 00:06:34,666
But I want to make amends
from the bottom of my heart

146
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:36,625
for belittling you
the way I did.

147
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:39,583
- Look, I'm sorry, but...

148
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:41,458
- Hmm?

149
00:06:41,541 --> 00:06:44,000
- I still hate
your freakin' guts.

150
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:45,916
I feel bad for what happened,

151
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,125
and I'm really grateful
you're here to help us out.

152
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:51,500
That said,
I honestly can't stand you.

153
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:53,958
I seriously hate you
from the bottom of my heart!

154
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:56,166
So there! [grumbles]

155
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,833
- [chuckles]

156
00:06:58,916 --> 00:06:59,958
Understandable.

157
00:07:00,041 --> 00:07:03,500
I'm quite certain I could
never befriend you, either.

158
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:04,125
Some things aren't meant to be.

159
00:07:04,208 --> 00:07:07,500
- [chuckles]
- [snaps reins]

160
00:07:07,583 --> 00:07:07,875
[Patrasche grunts]

161
00:07:07,958 --> 00:07:10,541
-<i> All right.</i>

162
00:07:10,625 --> 00:07:11,250
<i>As I say every time,</i>

163
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:14,041
<i>let's get this fight started.</i>

164
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:15,583
<i>Bring it on, fate.</i>

165
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:18,916
[birds chirping]

166
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,833
[doors open]

167
00:07:19,916 --> 00:07:22,250
[doors close]

168
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:32,416
- [energy warbles]
- [gasps]

169
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,708
You must be exhausted, Lia.

170
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:35,750
You should lie down
and rest for a bit.

171
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:38,500
- Mm-mmm.

172
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:41,500
I don't think that I'll
be able to fall asleep.

173
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:43,208
Aren't you
getting tired, though?

174
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:45,166
- No way. I'm fine.

175
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:47,583
The forest barrier
is all fixed up, too.

176
00:07:47,666 --> 00:07:48,708
You don't have
to worry about anything.

177
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:50,750
- [sighs]

178
00:07:52,375 --> 00:07:53,625
Even so...

179
00:07:54,875 --> 00:07:57,250
[brush rustling]

180
00:08:05,875 --> 00:08:06,875
- This feels a little bit
like the time

181
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:11,833
I found a big, ugly insect
in the corner of a quiet room.

182
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:13,375
So you guys are drawn
to the smell, huh?

183
00:08:13,458 --> 00:08:17,166
Looks like I'm
perfect cockroach bait.

184
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:18,125
Man, I must reek.

185
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:20,791
Thank you for meeting me.

186
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,791
I know you
just got here and all,

187
00:08:22,875 --> 00:08:25,875
but the business
that I need to discuss,

188
00:08:25,958 --> 00:08:28,916
it's really more a matter for
me
and your boss, not you guys,

189
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,208
so don't get in my way.

190
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:34,083
[sighs]

191
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:37,166
If they'd hung around and
waited
for just a little bit longer,

192
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,541
I could have told them
to pack up and go home.

193
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:40,833
Guess we'll do it
the hard way.

194
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:44,041
[panting]

195
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:47,166
[men's chorus chanting]

196
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:51,708
- I've been waiting
ever so patiently for you,

197
00:08:51,791 --> 00:08:52,583
believer in love.

198
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:54,916
I am a Sin Archbishop
of the Witch's cult

199
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,125
representing Sloth,

200
00:08:57,208 --> 00:09:00,625
Betelgeuse Romanée-Conti.

201
00:09:00,708 --> 00:09:01,000
[babbles]

202
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:02,291
I welcome you,

203
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:06,166
beloved child blessed with love.
[laughs]

204
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,666
Wonderful! [laughs]

205
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,208
Wonderful!

206
00:09:10,291 --> 00:09:12,291
[chorus vocalizing]

207
00:09:12,375 --> 00:09:13,583
- Hey.

208
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:17,083
I really appreciate
the unexpected welcome,

209
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:19,291
but I gotta admit
I'm not sure I really feel

210
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:20,416
all of this love
you keep bringing up.

211
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:23,791
- It always begins
suddenly out of the blue.

212
00:09:23,875 --> 00:09:25,000
Everyone on a certain day

213
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:27,958
comes to the realization
that they're indeed loved.

214
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:29,333
They feel it...

215
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:31,291
the love, the love, the love,
the love, the love,

216
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:33,125
the love, the love, the love...

217
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:37,291
- So what exactly
am I supposed to do now?

218
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:38,625
- Ah...

219
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:40,125
the most generous
love of the Witch.

220
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:43,541
Now tell me something, boy,

221
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:45,291
you wouldn't happen
to be Pride, would you?

222
00:09:45,375 --> 00:09:48,916
Out of the six Sin Archbishops
in total,

223
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:52,958
only the seat of Pride
remains unclaimed and vacant.

224
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:54,833
A query for you.

225
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:58,750
You have received the Gospel,
have you not?

226
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:00,125
- The Gospel?

227
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:01,875
[chorus continues]

228
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:04,000
- My brain... [sputters]

229
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:06,708
trembles! [groans]

230
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:08,000
- Eh?

231
00:10:08,083 --> 00:10:09,083
- Presentation of the Gospel.
- [flipping pages]

232
00:10:09,166 --> 00:10:11,708
Where is the proof of love?

233
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:12,750
[cackles] The proof!

234
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,166
The proof! The proof! The proof!

235
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:16,041
The proof! The proof!
The--[babbles]

236
00:10:16,125 --> 00:10:17,083
Huh?

237
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,916
There doesn't seem to be
an account of you

238
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,708
anywhere in my Gospel.

239
00:10:22,791 --> 00:10:23,333
-<i> That book is the Gospel?</i>

240
00:10:23,416 --> 00:10:26,166
- [wails] Explain yourself.

241
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,708
Why appear here before me?

242
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:29,708
Why visit
this place in particular?!

243
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:32,125
What fortune are you here
to bestow upon me, boy?!

244
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:34,125
Huh?!

245
00:10:34,208 --> 00:10:35,125
- Oh, wow.

246
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:36,041
So that's the Gospel.

247
00:10:36,125 --> 00:10:37,375
Yeah, I see. I see.

248
00:10:37,458 --> 00:10:40,875
Of course.
I understand completely.

249
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:43,208
You should have just said so
in the first place.

250
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:44,041
[patting]

251
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:45,208
Ah, darn it!

252
00:10:45,291 --> 00:10:47,000
My bad. I'm sorry.

253
00:10:47,083 --> 00:10:50,000
- About what?

254
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:51,750
- My Gospel is, well...

255
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:52,708
you see...

256
00:10:52,791 --> 00:10:56,458
I used it as a coaster,
and it got messy...

257
00:10:57,458 --> 00:10:59,250
so I threw it in the trash.

258
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:02,833
[music playing]

259
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:06,208
- Proof of love, nay!

260
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:10,083
Authority of Sloth!
Behold the Unseen Hand!

