you've done!

276
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:45,583
- How? How can this be?

277
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:49,333
My fingers so cruelly,
so mercilessly,

278
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:53,791
so chaotically,
so arbitrarily,

279
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:56,125
so artlessly,
so very meaninglessly...

280
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:59,500
[wailing]

281
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:01,958
My brain.

282
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:03,083
My brain trembles!

283
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:05,291
- Scary.

284
00:12:05,375 --> 00:12:07,125
That guy's
completely out of his mind.

285
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:09,291
- Pretty sure all the Witch's
Cultists are like that,

286
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:10,416
scary and crazy.

287
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:12,291
- Yes, of course.
It all makes sense.

288
00:12:12,375 --> 00:12:13,875
Yes, of course.
It all makes sense.

289
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:16,500
Yes, of course.
It all makes sense. [gasps]

290
00:12:16,583 --> 00:12:17,833
Yes. Fine!

291
00:12:17,916 --> 00:12:19,041
Yes. Fine! I understand.

292
00:12:19,125 --> 00:12:20,166
Let's do this!

293
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:22,125
I'm ready to do this!

294
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,125
I'm not afraid.

295
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:26,208
The time has come
to find out which one of us

296
00:12:26,291 --> 00:12:27,833
is worthy of her love!

297
00:12:27,916 --> 00:12:29,375
Worthy of her love, yes!

298
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:31,166
Her love!

299
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,166
- Sorry to interrupt
your screamy fun, but...

300
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:34,500
- Eh?

301
00:12:34,583 --> 00:12:36,750
- I've got someone else
lined up to take you on.

302
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:40,166
- Hyah!

303
00:12:47,583 --> 00:12:51,041
[thump]

304
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:53,375
SUBARU: I-It's over, right?

305
00:12:53,458 --> 00:12:54,375
He's dead?

306
00:12:54,458 --> 00:12:56,916
- Oh, yes, he's very much dead.

307
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,833
The most powerful healer
in the capital

308
00:12:58,916 --> 00:13:00,875
personally guarantees it.

309
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:02,333
- Right. Good.

310
00:13:02,416 --> 00:13:04,208
Thanks for that, Wilhelm.

311
00:13:04,291 --> 00:13:06,500
I hope it wasn't
asking too much.

312
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:09,166
- Really? What do you mean?

313
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:12,250
- Isn't cutting someone down
from behind without warning

314
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,916
like the worst thing
a knight can do?

315
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:18,125
- Chivalry is a code of conduct
that's long dead.

316
00:13:19,375 --> 00:13:20,958
You need not concern yourself
with that.

317
00:13:21,041 --> 00:13:22,541
- Hmm.

318
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:25,000
It doesn't look like this weirdo

319
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:27,041
was carrying
anything useful on him.

320
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:30,250
- Wow, you two little guys
are ransacking his corpse

321
00:13:30,333 --> 00:13:32,791
like it's not a big deal.
Kinda creepy.

322
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:34,916
- Look, I'm not little,
and the name's Tivey.

323
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,875
I believe
it's our right as victors

324
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:39,125
to search out
the spoils of battle.

325
00:13:39,208 --> 00:13:40,375
Hmm?

326
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:42,375
What is this?

327
00:13:42,458 --> 00:13:43,208
Some kind of book?

328
00:13:43,291 --> 00:13:45,791
SUBARU: Well, I think
that particular book

329
00:13:45,875 --> 00:13:47,833
is the one Betelgeuse
called the Gospel.

330
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:49,250
- [both gasp]
- You mean this is the Gospel?!

331
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:51,833
Oh, no! I-I touched it!

332
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:56,583
- I can't read it.

333
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:59,250
Do you know
what this says, Felix?

334
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:00,041
- [both gasp]
- No, wait!

335
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:02,125
Don't you point
that thing at me!

336
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,041
Why in the world
would you do something

337
00:14:03,125 --> 00:14:06,291
as stupid as trying to read
the Gospel, huh?

338
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:08,375
- Is it really that dangerous?

339
00:14:08,458 --> 00:14:09,875
Huh?

340
00:14:09,958 --> 00:14:11,208
WILHELM:
The Gospel is the proof

341
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,583
that one belongs
to the Witch's Cult.

342
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:16,958
It's basically what you'd call
their sacred text.

343
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:18,208
SUBARU: Their what?

344
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:19,916
FELIX: From what
the rumors say,

345
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,541
one of these is delivered
to anybody with the potential

346
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:23,833
to join the cult,

347
00:14:23,916 --> 00:14:26,583
and once a person gets it,
guess what.

348
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:29,250
They're neow a devout member
of the Witch's Cult,

349
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:30,583
just like that!

350
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:34,250
SUBARU: Man,
how shady can you get?

351
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:37,083
Well, I guess
I'll take this with me.

352
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:38,333
If I can decipher it,

353
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:41,458
maybe I can figure out what
the Witch's Cult really is.

354
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:43,458
- [gasps] Hey, hey!

355
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:45,458
Oh, listen, I know we've
killed the enemy here,

356
00:14:45,541 --> 00:14:47,958
but shouldn't we
take a look around and make sure

357
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:50,166
there aren't any other ones
to make dead, too?

358
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:52,500
- Yeah. You know,
as adorable as you might look,

359
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:55,916
you sure say some pretty weird
and disturbing things.

360
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,916
- [laughs] I'm adorable?
You're making me blush.

361
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,666
- So the subordinates
that Betelgeuse called fingers

362
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:04,208
number ten in total, correct?
That makes things easier.

363
00:15:04,291 --> 00:15:08,166
- I think one of those creeps is
pinned under this pile of rocks.

364
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:09,500
- Ten creeps minus one is nine!

365
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:11,333
That means nine creeps are left!

366
00:15:12,625 --> 00:15:14,208
- Well, then,
shall we find the others?

367
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:15,250
- [grunts]

368
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,666
Now, this freak of nature
is actually dead, right?

369
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,000
He's not gonna come back

370
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:26,875
the second we look away,
is he? [groans]

371
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:30,250
- Fine! If you're
that worried about it,

372
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:31,083
we'll make extra sure!

373
00:15:31,166 --> 00:15:32,750
- [gasps]

374
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:37,916
[overlapping chatter]

375
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,500
JULIUS: We crushed two
of the ones called fingers here.

376
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:42,416
A few of the cultists
were skilled,

377
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,625
but in the end,
they weren't a threat.

378
00:15:44,708 --> 00:15:47,416
It would seem we made no errors
in driving them off.

379
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,625
- I'm glad it went well
for you guys, too.

380
00:15:49,708 --> 00:15:51,083
JULIUS: Given your demeanor,

381
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:53,625
I can only assume
that your news is good as well.

382
00:15:53,708 --> 00:15:56,500
- Yep. Our group
took out Betelgeuse.

383
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:59,000
- That Subaru, he's a worrywart.

384
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:01,000
so that's why
we blew him to bits,

385
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:03,708
blasting that creep kaboom-style
after we killed him!

386
00:16:03,791 --> 00:16:04,708
- Whoa!

387
00:16:04,791 --> 00:16:06,000
- Nice work.

388
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:07,541
So that just leaves
the simple task

389
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:09,166
of mopping up
the remnants then, huh?

390
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:11,041
- We'd better hurry
and take care of 'em

391
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:13,625
before my beautiful lady
turns into an old granny.

392
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:14,458
Hey, what's going on?

393
00:16:14,541 --> 00:16:16,625
That was my best joke.

394
00:16:16,708 --> 00:16:18,541
[Mimi laughs]

395
00:16:18,625 --> 00:16:20,541
JULIUS: We rendezvous soon

396
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:21,875
with the dragon-drawn carriages
you arranged.

397
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:24,708
Let's eliminate
the remaining fingers

398
00:16:24,791 --> 00:16:27,666
and greet our victory
over this cult together.

399
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,750
- 'Kay, Subaru,
time for the bait.

400
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,125
Put out that smell.

401
00:16:31,208 --> 00:16:32,416
Neow breathe in.

402
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:35,083
- [inhales]
- And out.

403
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,416
- [exhales]
- And out!

404
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,291
- And out! And out!
- [gasping]

405
00:16:39,375 --> 00:16:41,541
Stop that!
I gotta breathe in, too!

406
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:44,166
- [laughter]

407
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:47,250
- So I guess...

408
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:50,125
- [laughter]
- once this is all done,

409
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:52,791
we'll just go back to being
friend and foe, won't we?

410
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:56,166
- How confident of you to worry
about what's yet to come.

411
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:56,791
- Hey, give me a break.

412
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:57,833
It's going almost too well,

413
00:16:57,916 --> 00:17:01,583
so maybe I let
my guard down a little.

414
00:17:01,666 --> 00:17:04,250
[gasps]

415
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:06,583
Get down now, all of you!

416
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:10,083
[Authority warbles]

417
00:17:17,625 --> 00:17:19,750
- What the hell?
